  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/50px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/75px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/100px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Meleys<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Red Queen</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/50px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/75px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/100px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Meleys.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Meleys.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/59/Meleys.png/350px-Meleys.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/59/Meleys.png/525px-Meleys.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/59/Meleys.png/700px-Meleys.png 2x\" /></a><div><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> on the back of Meleys, as depicted by Jordi Gonzalez Escamilla in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nthe Red Queen</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Owners</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Species</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">Dragon</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nIn&#160;before <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_75_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">75&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nIn&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>,&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_1\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 1\">Season 1</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">2</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Meleys</b>, called <b>the Red Queen</b>, was a she-<a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> ridden by Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and later Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Alyssa_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Alyssa Targaryen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Rhaenys_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rhaenys Targaryen</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_dragonriders_of_Meleys\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known dragonriders of Meleys</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Description\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Meleys\" title=\"Category:Images of Meleys\">Images of Meleys</a></div>\n<p>Meleys had scarlet scales and pink membranes on her wings, for which she received her alias, <i>the Red Queen</i>. Her crest, horns, and claws were bright as <a href=\"/index.php/Copper\" title=\"Copper\">copper</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The dragon was described as \"splendid\" and \"magnificent\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_75_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">75&#160;AC</a>, Meleys was considered to be one of the swiftest dragons in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, easily outpacing <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> By <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, Meleys had grown lazy, but was still fearsome when roused<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and cunning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Alyssa_Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Alyssa Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/78/Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg/400px-Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/78/Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg/600px-Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/78/Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg/800px-Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Viserys%27s_first_flight_by_Rene_Aigner.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a> takes her son  <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys</a> on his first flight on Meleys. Art by René Aigner © for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>By <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_75_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">75&#160;AC</a>, Meleys resided in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, never ridden before. That year, the newly married Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a> decided to become a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonrider</a>. She initially wished to claim <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion\" title=\"Balerion\">Balerion</a>, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonkeepers\" title=\"Dragonkeepers\">dragonkeepers</a> convinced her that he was too old and slow, and that she would prefer a swifter mount. Alyssa claimed Meleys, and afterwards rarely stayed away from the Dragonpit for long. The dragon was indeed as swift as promised, easily besting the dragons of Alyssa's brothers <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Jaehaerys_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Jaehaerys I)\">Aemon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Baelon_Targaryen\" title=\"Baelon Targaryen\">Baelon</a> when they flew together.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_77_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">77&#160;AC</a>, Alyssa strapped her nine-day old son <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys</a> to her chest and took him flying on Meleys. She did the same in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_81_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">81&#160;AC</a> with her second son, <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon</a>, within a fortnight of his birth. In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_84_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">84&#160;AC</a>, Meleys became riderless when Princess Alyssa died some time after a difficult labor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rhaenys_Targaryen\">Rhaenys Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Rhaenys Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ee/Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/350px-Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"247\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ee/Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/525px-Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ee/Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/700px-Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Meleys_the_Red_Queen_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Meleys the Red Queen, ridden by Rhaenys Targaryen. Art by Jota Saraiva ©</div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_87_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">87&#160;AC</a>, Meleys was claimed by Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_89_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">89&#160;AC</a>, Rhaenys flew on Meleys to <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a>, to accompany King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> further on his <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Shield_Islands\" title=\"Shield Islands\">Shield Islands</a>. When Rhaenys married Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_90_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">90&#160;AC</a>, she insisted on arriving to the wedding flying on Meleys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Princess Rhaenys rode Meleys during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, on the side of Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>, versus King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a>. When the <a href=\"/index.php/Velaryon_fleet\" title=\"Velaryon fleet\">Velaryon fleet</a> closed off the <a href=\"/index.php/Gullet\" title=\"Gullet\">Gullet</a>, sailing forth from <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a> to block all shipping for <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Bay\" title=\"Blackwater Bay\">Blackwater Bay</a>, the blacks' plan was for Rhaenys to fly overhead on Meleys to keep the greens from attacking the ships with their dragons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png/350px-Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"519\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png/525px-Death_of_Rhaenys.png 1.5x, /images/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The bodies of Rhaenys and Meleys, as depicted by Douglas Wheatley in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>.</div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, when <a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a> was besieged by the greens' army led by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a>, Rhaenys flew Meleys to the castle to lend aid. During the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Battle at Rook&#39;s Rest\">battle at Rook's Rest</a>, Meleys was attacked by Cole's archers and shot with iron bolts by <a href=\"/index.php/Armament#Siege_Weapons\" title=\"Armament\">scorpions</a>, which angered her but did not do her harm. In response, she spat fire on the men below, and attacked the knights and horses, killing about 800 men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>However, the battle proved to be a ploy when King Aegon and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a> suddenly appeared upon <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> above Rook's Rest. Rhaenys turned to meet the attack, despite the knowledge that Meleys had no hope of success against the two dragons. According to Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a>, Meleys might have stood a chance against the older Vhagar alone, but not against Vhagar and Sunfyre combined. The dragons met violently in the air, a thousand feet above the field, with their fireballs bursting as bright as the sun. Meleys managed to close her jaw around Sunfyre's neck, just as Vhagar fell upon them, and all three dragons fell from the sky. They crashed to the ground so hard that stones fell from the battlements of Rook's Rest, half a league away.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>From the ashes, only Aemond and Vhagar rose unharmed. Meleys had half torn one of Sunfyre's wings off,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and Aegon suffered broken ribs, a broken hip, and burns that covered half his body. Meleys did not survive the fall, and was ripped to pieces when she hit the ground. A body believed to be Rhaenys Targaryen was found beside the carcass of her dragon, so blackened that she was impossible to identify. The head of Meleys was brought back to King's Landing by the forces of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> and drawn on a <a href=\"/index.php/Cart\" title=\"Cart\">cart</a> through the city, a display that awed the <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> into silence. According to Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace\" title=\"Eustace\">Eustace</a>, thousands left King's Landing afterward, until Dowager Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> ordered the city gates closed and barred.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_dragonriders_of_Meleys\">Known dragonriders of Meleys</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known dragonriders of Meleys\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Red <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden\" title=\"Maiden\">maidens</a>, the two of us, but now we've both been mounted.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Alyssa_Targaryen\" title=\"Alyssa Targaryen\">Alyssa Targaryen</a> about herself and Meleys, after claiming the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>With a glad cry and a crack of her whip, she turned Meleys toward the foe.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of Gyldayn, about <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_Rook%27s_Rest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle of Rook&#39;s Rest\">battle of Rook's Rest</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_J._Peterson\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:David J. Peterson\">David J. Peterson</a>, the official language creator for the television adaptations of Martin's works, devised the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Valyrian\" title=\"High Valyrian\">High Valyrian</a> word for the color red, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://wiki.languageinvention.com/index.php?title=mele\"><i>mele</i></a>, from the inspiration of Meleys and <a href=\"/index.php/Melisandre\" title=\"Melisandre\">Melisandre</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Meleys&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D